tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, suggesting impaired glucose metabolism or early diabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Hemoglobin and hematocrit are slightly high, which may indicate dehydration, polycythemia, or other causes. Platelet distribution width is markedly elevated, possibly reflecting platelet activation or variation. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation are recommended.
